# Ron Group LLC Internal Software License

## 1. Introduction

This document outlines the terms under which employees of Ron Group LLC ("the Company") may use, contribute to, and distribute the software and documentation contained within this repository. The goal is to foster an open, collaborative environment akin to open-source development, yet restrict the software's use and distribution to within the Company.

## 2. Grant of License

Subject to the terms and conditions of this License, the Company hereby grants to each employee a non-exclusive, non-transferable right to use, modify, and contribute to the software and documentation within this repository for any purpose related to the employee's work at the Company.

## 3. Contributions

Employees are encouraged to contribute to the software, provided that any such contributions are made under the same terms and conditions of this License. All contributions become the property of the Company.

## 4. Restrictions

-	The software and documentation may only be used for internal projects and purposes directly related to the employee's work at the Company.
-	The software and documentation may not be copied, modified, distributed, or used in any manner outside of the Company without prior written permission from an authorized representative of the Company.
-	No licenses are granted to any patents, trademarks, copyrights, or other forms of intellectual property owned by the Company, except as explicitly stated herein.

## 5. Disclaimer of Warranty

The software and documentation are provided "as is" without warranty of any kind, express or implied. The Company makes no warranties regarding the software's performance, fitness for a particular purpose, or reliability.

## 6. Limitation of Liability

The Company shall not be liable for any claims, damages, or other liabilities arising from the use of the software and documentation, except as mandated by law.

## 7. General

This License is governed by the laws of South Carolina, without regard to conflict of law principles. This License constitutes the entire agreement between the employee and the Company concerning the software and supersedes any prior agreements or understandings.

By using, modifying, or contributing to the software and documentation within this repository, you, the employee, agree to be bound by the terms of this License.
